	  <td width="100" valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'><b> Hello time</b></td>
        <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>The hello time is the time between each BPDU frame that is sent on a port. <br />This is equal to 2 seconds by default, but can be tuned to be between 1 and 10 seconds. </td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td width="100" valign='top' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'><b>Forward delay</b></td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#DDDDDD' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>The forward delay is the time spent in the listening and learning state. <br />This is by default equal to 15 seconds for each state, but can be tuned to be between 4 and 30 seconds. </td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#F2F2F2">
	  <td width="100" valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'><b>Maximum age</b></td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>The max age timer controls the maximum length of time a switch port saves configuration BPDU information. <br />This is 20 seconds by default, but can be tuned to be between 6 and 40 seconds. </td>
  </tr>
